<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4610840>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 36. Occusal stereopairs of the holotype mandibles of (A, C) Delotrochanter oryktes (ACM 4804) and (B, D) Delotrochanter major (F:AM 27561). D. oryktes, right p4–m2, alveoli of p1–3; D. major, left p2– m2. Note absence of m1 metaconids and relative anterior and posterior alveolar diameters of p2 in D. oryktes. The p4–m2 are crushing teeth in both species." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4610840/files/figure.png" .

